{
  "document_id": "prov-19",
  "title": "Proverbs 19",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "Oxford",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-heading-20",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "20"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Desire without knowledge is not good, and one who moves too hurriedly misses the way."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "One's own folly leads to ruin, yet the heart rages against the Lord."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "3 : Fools refuse to take responsibility for themselves (cf. Sir 15.11–20).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 3,
      "verse_end": 3
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Wealth brings many friends, but the poor are left friendless."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "4 : The impact of on relationships; see vv. 6–7; 14.20–21; 10.15n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 4,
      "verse_end": 4
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "A false witness will not go unpunished, and a liar will not escape."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "5 : , see 12.17n. See v. 9.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 5,
      "verse_end": 5
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Many seek the favor of the generous, and everyone is a friend to a giver of gifts."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "If the poor are hated even by their kin, how much more are they shunned by their friends! When they call after them, they are not there."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "To get wisdom is to love oneself; to keep understanding is to prosper."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-6",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "8 : See 10.2–3n.; cf. 15.32.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 8,
      "verse_end": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "A false witness will not go unpunished, and the liar will perish."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "It is not fitting for a fool to live in luxury, much less for a slave to rule over princes."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-7",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10 : , see 17.7n. A portrait of the world turned upside down; see 30.21–22; Eccl 10.6–7.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 10,
      "verse_end": 10
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Those with good sense are slow to anger, and it is their glory to overlook an offense."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-8",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "11 : , see 12.16n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 11,
      "verse_end": 11
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "A king's anger is like the growling of a lion, but his favor is like dew on the grass."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-9",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "12 : Royal wrath and favor as forces of nature (cf. 16.14–15; 20.2). Kings were associated with lions in the ancient Near East (e.g., Judg 14.5–6; 1 Sam 7.34–36; 1 Kings 10.19–20; Jer 50.17; Ezek 32.2–3).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 12
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "A stupid child is ruin to a father, and a wife's quarreling is a continual dripping of rain."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "House and wealth are inherited from parents, but a prudent wife is from the Lord."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-10",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "13–14 : Sources of household suffering and joy from a male perspective. , see 21.9,19; 25.24; 27.15–16. , see 12.4n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 13,
      "verse_end": 14
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Laziness brings on deep sleep; an idle person will suffer hunger."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-11",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "15 : , see 6.9–11n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 15,
      "verse_end": 15
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Those who keep the commandment will live; those who are heedless of their ways will die."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-12",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "16 : (Heb “mitswah”) in Proverbs typically refers to wisdom instruction (e.g., 2.1; 3.1; 4.4; 6.20,23; 13.13).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 16,
      "verse_end": 16
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Whoever is kind to the poor lends to the Lord, and will be repaid in full."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-13",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "17 : See 14.31n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 17,
      "verse_end": 17
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Discipline your children while there is hope; do not set your heart on their destruction."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "A violent tempered person will pay the penalty; if you effect a rescue, you will only have to do it again.d"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-14",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "19 : , see 12.16n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 19,
      "verse_end": 19
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Listen to advice and accept instruction, that you may gain wisdom for the future."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "The human mind may devise many plans, but it is the purpose of the Lord that will be established."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-15",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21 : God's sovereignty, see 16.1–9; 20.24; 21.30–31.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 21,
      "verse_end": 21
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "What is desirable in a person is loyalty, and it is better to be poor than a liar."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-16",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "22 : , see 12.9n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 22,
      "verse_end": 22
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is life indeed; filled with it one rests secure and suffers no harm."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-17",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "23 : , see 1.7n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 23,
      "verse_end": 23
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "The lazy person buries a hand in the dish, and will not even bring it back to the mouth."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-18",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "24 : , see 6.9–11n., cf. 26.15.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 24,
      "verse_end": 24
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Strike a scoffer, and the simple will learn prudence; reprove the intelligent, and they will gain knowledge."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-19",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "25 : , see 1.22n.; 9.7–12; 15.12; 21.11.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 25,
      "verse_end": 25
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Those who do violence to their father and chase away their mother are children who cause shame and bring reproach."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-20",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "26 : See 28.24n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 26,
      "verse_end": 26
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Cease straying, my child, from the words of knowledge, in order that you may hear instruction."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "A worthless witness mocks at justice, and the mouth of the wicked devours iniquity."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Condemnation is ready for scoffers, and flogging for the backs of fools."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-19-h1kj-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10.1–22.16: The proverbs of Solomon. Comprised predominantly of two-line proverbs, the oldest section of Proverbs can be divided into 10.1–15.33, which features antithetical proverbs, and 16.1–22.16, which includes a mix of proverbial forms.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 19
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 29
    }
  ]
}